cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CV 

This paper deals with natural language understanding and machine translation, which are typically covered under the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper specifically focuses on developing compositional vector space models of meaning, which are commonly used in computational linguistics and machine learning research. Therefore, cs.CL and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also uses automatic extraction of paraphrase examples, which involves natural language processing techniques, and develops a context-aware model for scoring phrasal compositionality, which involves machine learning techniques. Hence, cs.AI and cs.IR are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates the impact of its approaches on machine translation, which is a task that involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques and is often covered under the sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV).
